1
00:00:09,343 --> 00:00:11,073
You're bleeding
through your bandage.

2
00:00:17,284 --> 00:00:18,377
Good morning.

3
00:00:18,752 --> 00:00:21,187
Don't we need to
get you to a doctor?

4
00:00:21,255 --> 00:00:24,919
I am a doctor. That
didn't come up last night?

5
00:00:25,526 --> 00:00:27,085
We didn't do a lot of talking.

6
00:00:43,277 --> 00:00:44,711
I'm good.

7
00:00:57,057 --> 00:00:59,253
You never told me what
caused your accident.

8
00:01:00,994 --> 00:01:03,122
I was stabbed by a patient.

9
00:01:03,630 --> 00:01:05,098
That'll teach me to overbill.

10
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:42,634
If she likes crippled guys, I'm
free for the next six minutes.

11
00:01:42,703 --> 00:01:43,864
What do you want?

12
00:01:44,705 --> 00:01:46,537
Forty-five year-old
truck driver.

13
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:48,905
Recurrent seizures, no
metabolic or structural...

14
00:01:49,009 --> 00:01:50,307
Does this look like a good time?

15
00:01:51,411 --> 00:01:53,505
Sort of. At least as
good as the other

16
00:01:53,580 --> 00:01:55,058
12 times that I've
called and paged you

17
00:01:55,082 --> 00:01:56,175
in the last three weeks.

18
00:01:56,249 --> 00:01:57,594
Those times, I
just didn't feel like

19
00:01:57,618 --> 00:01:59,177
talking to you. Kinda like now.

20
00:01:59,419 --> 00:02:01,513
I'd apologize again,
but I'm still waiting

21
00:02:01,588 --> 00:02:03,716
for you to accept the first one.

22
00:02:04,858 --> 00:02:07,760
You do work for me. I am entitled
to ask when you're coming back.

23
00:02:07,861 --> 00:02:09,227
I don't know when
I'm coming back.

24
00:02:09,363 --> 00:02:10,729
I don't know if I'm coming back.

25
00:02:11,431 --> 00:02:14,230
Got a problem
with that? Fire me.

26
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:07,444
It's good to see
you in the hospital.

27
00:03:07,587 --> 00:03:09,146
As a patient, if
not as a doctor.

28
00:03:09,256 --> 00:03:13,717
Believe me, I'd rather be
the guy with the clipboard.

29
00:03:15,962 --> 00:03:17,055
How you doing?

30
00:03:19,232 --> 00:03:22,566
Arrhythmias are gone, fine
motor control's improving.

31
00:03:22,636 --> 00:03:23,899
Not what I meant.

32
00:03:25,939 --> 00:03:29,706
If you need to talk to
someone, a professional...

33
00:03:30,310 --> 00:03:31,903
I'm fine.

34
00:03:33,213 --> 00:03:34,493
Fine enough to get back to work?

35
00:03:37,951 --> 00:03:39,228
You don't have
to work for House,

36
00:03:39,252 --> 00:03:41,118
but you do owe
me 20 clinic hours.

37
00:03:41,755 --> 00:03:44,122
What? Getting knifed
doesn't buy me an extension?

38
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:47,956
Buys you whatever you
need. But I know you.

39
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:49,859
If all you do is
physical therapy,

40
00:03:49,996 --> 00:03:51,828
and your nighttime
version of it,

41
00:03:52,432 --> 00:03:55,994
you'll lose your mind faster than
you regain those fine motor skills.

42
00:04:07,314 --> 00:04:12,753
I have this terrible pain in my left
shoulder. It came out of nowhere.

43
00:04:12,819 --> 00:04:14,947
And nothing seems to help.

44
00:04:19,593 --> 00:04:23,496
Any other symptoms? Chest
pain? Light-headedness?

45
00:04:23,597 --> 00:04:25,463
No, none at all.

46
00:04:25,532 --> 00:04:27,172
What were you doing
when the pain came on?

47
00:04:27,501 --> 00:04:29,163
Just sitting and praying.

48
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:30,880
She'd been helping to
make the altar breads

49
00:04:30,904 --> 00:04:32,770
that morning, but no
hard physical work,

50
00:04:32,839 --> 00:04:34,535
or repetitive motion.

51
00:04:34,674 --> 00:04:36,370
Couple of possibilities.

52
00:04:36,476 --> 00:04:37,944
You have enlarged
lymph nodes, so

53
00:04:38,011 --> 00:04:39,811
I'd like to start by
ruling out breast cancer.

54
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:43,612
And I do mean rule
out. It's probably nothing.

55
00:04:44,618 --> 00:04:46,246
I'm gonna do a
quick breast exam.

56
00:04:46,319 --> 00:04:48,254
Do you mind stepping
out for a moment?

57
00:04:49,856 --> 00:04:51,381
Not at all.

58
00:04:56,163 --> 00:04:58,243
That was so I could ask
about the second possibility.

59
00:04:58,899 --> 00:05:03,064
Left-sided pain means it could be
angina, which is made worse by stress.

60
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:05,036
Might not be a
coincidence that the pain

61
00:05:05,105 --> 00:05:07,506
started on the verge
of a major life change.

62
00:05:08,408 --> 00:05:09,408
How did you know?

63
00:05:09,676 --> 00:05:11,076
Blue veil means
you're a postulant,

64
00:05:11,511 --> 00:05:12,809
haven't taken your vows yet.

65
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,540
Brown vestments
means you're Carmelites,

66
00:05:15,649 --> 00:05:18,312
cloistered nuns, which
explains the chaperone.

67
00:05:21,388 --> 00:05:23,323
You're about to withdraw
from the world for good.

68
00:05:24,991 --> 00:05:26,721
I was a seminarian.

69
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:28,590
Who obviously
didn't take his vows.

70
00:05:28,995 --> 00:05:30,520
Cassock made my ass look fat.

71
00:05:32,899 --> 00:05:35,164
Do you mind unbuttoning your
shirt and lying down for me?

72
00:05:35,235 --> 00:05:36,567
Okay.

73
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:42,404
I have had second
thoughts. I'm kind of a wreck.

74
00:05:45,412 --> 00:05:48,405
A life of perpetual enclosure
and almost complete silence?

75
00:05:48,915 --> 00:05:50,126
If you weren't
wrestling with this,

76
00:05:50,150 --> 00:05:53,018
I'd say there's something
really wrong with you.

77
00:05:57,958 --> 00:05:59,893
I'm going to admit you.

78
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:02,440
There's a little mass here,
and I'd like to get it checked out.

79
00:06:04,731 --> 00:06:07,633
It's just a benign fat
deposit, her imaging's clean.

80
00:06:07,734 --> 00:06:11,967
Stress test, too. It's not angina.
So why the shoulder pain?

81
00:06:12,072 --> 00:06:16,237
Is it possible that
she hurt her shoulder?

82
00:06:16,743 --> 00:06:17,743
Thanks a lot.

83
00:06:17,878 --> 00:06:18,878
I didn't tell him.

84
00:06:18,945 --> 00:06:20,937
You were cagey about
where you were going,

85
00:06:21,081 --> 00:06:23,073
and Chase has been
cagey in general.

86
00:06:23,149 --> 00:06:25,311
Good chance I'd find the
two of you in the same cage,

87
00:06:25,719 --> 00:06:27,210
so I had Park follow you.

88
00:06:29,256 --> 00:06:30,554
How are you feeling?

89
00:06:30,690 --> 00:06:31,988
Better.

90
00:06:32,092 --> 00:06:33,583
Heard your arm's healing nicely.

91
00:06:34,628 --> 00:06:35,891
Good to see you on your feet.

92
00:06:36,029 --> 00:06:37,292
Patient's a nun?

93
00:06:37,964 --> 00:06:40,763
Were you turning back to your
long-abandoned faith in time of trouble?

94
00:06:40,834 --> 00:06:44,168
She was next up in the clinic.
And I don't want your help.

95
00:06:44,271 --> 00:06:47,400
You got stabbed, you blame me.

96
00:06:48,642 --> 00:06:50,372
But what did you learn about me

97
00:06:50,443 --> 00:06:51,968
that you hadn't known for years?

98
00:06:52,178 --> 00:06:54,170
Maybe I was an idiot
before, and I'm not one now.

99
00:06:54,281 --> 00:06:56,011
Or maybe the reverse is true.

100
00:06:56,983 --> 00:06:58,076
Thanks for all your help.

101
00:07:04,925 --> 00:07:08,089
Your soul sister is
having a fungal infection

102
00:07:08,161 --> 00:07:11,256
from the unprocessed
wheat in the altar breads.

103
00:07:11,331 --> 00:07:14,768
Explains the shoulder pain
and the jumbo lymph nodes.

104
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:24,805
Thanks for all my help.

105
00:07:27,948 --> 00:07:30,383
I'm sorry I led House to you.

106
00:07:31,151 --> 00:07:33,313
It's part of the job.

107
00:07:33,386 --> 00:07:35,753
Maybe we could get a
meal after work tonight

108
00:07:35,889 --> 00:07:38,290
if you want some companionship.

109
00:07:40,327 --> 00:07:42,387
You asking me out on a date?

110
00:07:42,662 --> 00:07:46,190
No. I just... I guess
that sounded...

111
00:07:48,068 --> 00:07:52,802
Must be scary to be back.
All those knives and needles,

112
00:07:52,872 --> 00:07:55,967
infected blood and tissue
everywhere you look.

113
00:07:57,377 --> 00:08:00,313
Just thought you might need
someone to talk to about it.

114
00:08:01,047 --> 00:08:04,575
Just knowing you're there
for me is enough. Thanks.

115
00:08:11,057 --> 00:08:12,525
Ever surf Kirra Point?

116
00:08:14,828 --> 00:08:16,660
Obviously you're Australian.

117
00:08:18,098 --> 00:08:22,092
I've surfed all over the Gold
Coast. Don't tell me you have.

118
00:08:22,202 --> 00:08:26,162
The closest I got was
Waimea Bay. I grew up on Maui.

119
00:08:29,409 --> 00:08:32,675
If you don't mind me asking,
why are you becoming a nun?

120
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:35,344
You're asking because I surf?

121
00:08:35,849 --> 00:08:38,478
Well, I know that Jesus
walked on water, but...

122
00:08:39,019 --> 00:08:41,614
Plus the average postulant's
a lot younger than you.

123
00:08:42,756 --> 00:08:44,691
What were you doing before this?

124
00:08:44,758 --> 00:08:47,284
Not much of anything.
Worked as a nanny,

125
00:08:47,394 --> 00:08:49,829
moved around a lot,
bunch of failed relationships.

126
00:08:50,296 --> 00:08:54,825
And then what? God spoke
to you? You heard the calling?

127
00:08:56,336 --> 00:08:58,168
Something like that.

128
00:09:00,473 --> 00:09:03,238
Does there have to be some
dramatic moment where the skies part?

129
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:05,503
Usually, yeah.

130
00:09:05,612 --> 00:09:08,605
Is that what happened to you
when you entered the seminary?

131
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:15,684
Mom drank, Dad worked,
they stuck me in Catholic school.

132
00:09:15,789 --> 00:09:18,953
Priests and nuns were
the closest I had to family.

133
00:09:19,025 --> 00:09:21,470
Turned out that wasn't much of
a reason to join the priesthood.

134
00:09:21,494 --> 00:09:23,156
Is that why you left?

135
00:09:25,198 --> 00:09:26,598
Something like that.

136
00:09:34,007 --> 00:09:36,033
I think I may throw up.

137
00:09:46,953 --> 00:09:49,184
What's wrong with me?

138
00:09:49,989 --> 00:09:52,584
Not a fungal infection.

139
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:03,301
You're probably wondering,
why the soda balloons.

140
00:10:03,369 --> 00:10:04,769
I'm not.

141
00:10:04,838 --> 00:10:07,535
Well, I'll tell you.
You're not the only one

142
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:09,303
whose life spiraled
out of control

143
00:10:09,375 --> 00:10:10,843
when you got
knifed in the ventricle.

144
00:10:10,944 --> 00:10:12,139
Taub has decided...

145
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:13,473
I need help with my patient.

146
00:10:13,546 --> 00:10:16,277
She's vomiting. That's
not from a fungal infection.

147
00:10:16,349 --> 00:10:17,560
So what are you
planning to do now

148
00:10:17,584 --> 00:10:18,761
that you're not working for me?

149
00:10:18,785 --> 00:10:20,310
I have no idea.

150
00:10:21,154 --> 00:10:23,885
Almost dying's been
clarifying. I can do anything.

151
00:10:23,957 --> 00:10:26,927
You can do anything,
so you come back to

152
00:10:26,993 --> 00:10:29,258
the same building you
worked in for years?

153
00:10:30,196 --> 00:10:31,996
Guess you can cross
that off your bucket list.

154
00:10:32,031 --> 00:10:33,863
Can we get to my
patient sometime soon?

155
00:10:33,967 --> 00:10:37,802
As soon as you admit that
you're a confused mess, sure.

156
00:10:37,871 --> 00:10:39,430
You'll help me.
Because even though

157
00:10:39,506 --> 00:10:40,850
you don't find my
case interesting,

158
00:10:40,874 --> 00:10:42,900
you find my interest
in it interesting.

159
00:10:45,078 --> 00:10:49,345
When you put it that way...
Ascending cholangitis.

160
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:55,013
Missed me!

161
00:10:55,088 --> 00:10:57,421
It can't be, bilirubin's normal.

162
00:10:58,258 --> 00:11:01,717
Clinical signs can show
up days before lab signs.

163
00:11:06,199 --> 00:11:09,067
This is great, we should
make this a regular thing.

164
00:11:12,906 --> 00:11:14,499
She can't feel her foot at all.

165
00:11:19,112 --> 00:11:20,603
What does this mean?

166
00:11:21,681 --> 00:11:25,413
Means I've gotta spend more
time consulting with a colleague.

167
00:11:30,723 --> 00:11:34,455
His 17-ketosteroid levels
are low. How can he be...

168
00:11:34,561 --> 00:11:37,258
He tried to tongue-kiss
Park when you were closer.

169
00:11:37,630 --> 00:11:39,326
Think his sexuality's normal?

170
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:43,029
I need more help. My patient
has a new symptom, ischemic foot.

171
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:46,901
Get the lecture out of your system,
so we can talk about my case.

172
00:11:49,075 --> 00:11:52,068
Let me start with an allegory...

173
00:11:59,285 --> 00:12:01,083
Okay, I'm curious...

174
00:12:02,155 --> 00:12:04,624
Your overreaction
to your stabbing is

175
00:12:04,757 --> 00:12:07,249
to blame me even
as you're drawn to me.

176
00:12:07,327 --> 00:12:10,889
Taub's is to take moronic
self-defense classes

177
00:12:10,964 --> 00:12:13,900
that won't defend
him against anything.

178
00:12:13,967 --> 00:12:16,630
Krav Maga. Which
helped me block your shot,

179
00:12:16,736 --> 00:12:18,376
and will continue to
help me defend myself

180
00:12:18,504 --> 00:12:20,184
in a building full of
drugged-up strangers.

181
00:12:20,273 --> 00:12:23,675
Taub has to accept that
by instinct and genetics,

182
00:12:23,776 --> 00:12:25,574
he is a coward,
who's better off running

183
00:12:25,712 --> 00:12:27,544
and hiding at the
first sign of danger.

184
00:12:27,647 --> 00:12:30,310
I've already fended off six
of your blitzkriegs in a row.

185
00:12:30,383 --> 00:12:33,547
And the seventh? And
the eighth? And the nth?

186
00:12:33,653 --> 00:12:35,485
If you get him, what's
that gonna prove?

187
00:12:35,555 --> 00:12:37,319
That unexpected things happen.

188
00:12:37,790 --> 00:12:40,521
By definition, no class can
teach you to expect them.

189
00:12:41,127 --> 00:12:43,153
Which is why Taub
is idiotic to study them,

190
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:45,721
and you're idiotic to attach
any significance to them.

191
00:12:46,366 --> 00:12:47,366
Blood clot.

192
00:12:48,001 --> 00:12:49,799
Her D-dimer's normal.

193
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:52,298
On the other hand...

194
00:12:58,845 --> 00:13:01,405
What if he's right about the
blockage, but wrong about the cause?

195
00:13:01,848 --> 00:13:03,043
Vasospasm.

196
00:13:03,383 --> 00:13:05,284
Explain everything
but the lymph nodes...

197
00:13:05,852 --> 00:13:07,572
Any minor infection
could have caused those.

198
00:13:07,654 --> 00:13:10,180
Calcium channel
blocker to treat.

199
00:13:21,334 --> 00:13:23,326
Are you okay?

200
00:13:23,403 --> 00:13:26,066
I almost got you killed by
bringing a scalpel into that room.

201
00:13:26,172 --> 00:13:28,869
I could feel better about
that. You saved my life, too.

202
00:13:29,542 --> 00:13:31,340
I think the ledger's clear.

203
00:13:33,179 --> 00:13:35,114
But how can you
not be traumatized?

204
00:13:35,248 --> 00:13:37,217
Can't change what happened.

205
00:13:37,450 --> 00:13:40,249
I can only make better
choices from here.

206
00:13:40,353 --> 00:13:43,846
So you're Zen about it, but won't
let go of your anger toward House.

207
00:13:47,193 --> 00:13:50,527
I'm seeing a trauma counselor.
I think you should, too.

208
00:13:51,064 --> 00:13:54,933
I'm okay. Just knowing
you're there for me is enough.

209
00:14:04,210 --> 00:14:06,042
The convent lets you have this?

210
00:14:06,112 --> 00:14:08,445
I borrowed it from
one of the nurses.

211
00:14:09,082 --> 00:14:10,311
I'm still on temporary vows.

212
00:14:10,383 --> 00:14:12,784
It may be the last time I
hear Eminem for a while.

213
00:14:14,087 --> 00:14:18,218
You're using an iPod, but I've
never seen you use rosary beads.

214
00:14:23,262 --> 00:14:25,629
What day did Jesus die?

215
00:14:25,732 --> 00:14:30,067
I know, one gospel says Passover,
another says the day before.

216
00:14:30,136 --> 00:14:33,664
How many times did the cock
crow before Peter's third denial?

217
00:14:33,773 --> 00:14:35,469
Once or twice?

218
00:14:35,608 --> 00:14:37,304
You can't argue away my faith.

219
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:41,404
Why? Because it's so strong
even plain contradictions...

220
00:14:41,481 --> 00:14:43,143
Because it's not that strong.

221
00:14:45,184 --> 00:14:47,779
I'm not saying I
don't have faith.

222
00:14:48,488 --> 00:14:50,821
I just haven't felt
the calling yet.

223
00:14:50,923 --> 00:14:54,155
No one joins the clergy
without having an epiphany.

224
00:14:54,260 --> 00:14:56,695
Like God's love is
speaking to you directly.

225
00:14:57,096 --> 00:15:02,091
It's the silence, the
contemplation, the order.

226
00:15:03,369 --> 00:15:04,496
I need them.

227
00:15:07,807 --> 00:15:09,673
I'm hoping everything
else will come later.

228
00:15:10,143 --> 00:15:15,047
That's not an answer. If you
want silence, you can get earplugs.

229
00:15:15,148 --> 00:15:18,710
I tried the outside
world. It wasn't enough.

230
00:15:18,985 --> 00:15:21,318
Have you been married? No.

231
00:15:21,387 --> 00:15:23,288
No kids? You never
found a career?

232
00:15:23,356 --> 00:15:25,882
Doesn't sound like the
outside world got much of a try.

233
00:15:28,361 --> 00:15:30,796
What you're headed
towards now...

234
00:15:31,497 --> 00:15:33,693
Fourteen hours a
day in silent prayer,

235
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,025
never having a family,

236
00:15:36,269 --> 00:15:38,295
never touching
another human being...

237
00:15:38,371 --> 00:15:40,863
Just because that's what
you'd miss the most...

238
00:15:42,975 --> 00:15:45,137
The nurses talk.

239
00:15:48,981 --> 00:15:50,347
Nothing's wrong with having fun.

240
00:15:51,050 --> 00:15:54,077
They said you were almost
killed three weeks ago.

241
00:15:54,187 --> 00:15:55,985
You go right back to fun?

242
00:15:57,089 --> 00:16:00,582
Is that why you want to be a
nun? Someone broke your heart?

243
00:16:01,561 --> 00:16:03,223
No.

244
00:16:05,598 --> 00:16:08,727
I'm just looking for
something more.

245
00:16:11,337 --> 00:16:12,566
So am I.

246
00:16:23,115 --> 00:16:25,584
I'm late for work in the clinic.

247
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:46,730
